<h2>Autoresize examples</h2>
<h3>Dynamic auto resize</h3>
<p>It uses the <a href="https://github.com/tim-evans/ember-autoresize" target="_blank">Ember AutoResize</a> addon. You can install it: <em>ember install ember-autoresize</em>. And then set autoResize property to true.</p>
<div class="row examples-header">
  <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">Output</div>
  <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">Code</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
    <div class="multi-line-text-wrapper">
      {{ember-inplace-edit
        text=(nl2br multiLineText)
        value=multiLineText
        type="textarea"
        placeholder="Add Placeholder content"
        placeholderClass="placeholder div class"
        editIcon="hide"
        autoResize=true
      }}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
{{#code-block language='handlebars'}}\{{ember-inplace-edit
  text=(nl2br multiLineText)
  value=multiLineText
  type="textarea"
  placeholder="Add Placeholder content"
  placeholderClass="placeholder div class"
  editIcon="hide"
  autoResize=true
}}{{/code-block}}
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Static resize</h3>
<p>This is the default behavoiur, it sets the height and the widht of the textarea right after the editing has been started, but it won't update them as content changes.</p>
